1.10	IFFHS_World's_Best_Goalkeeper	IFFHS World's Best Goalkeeper	The IFFHS World's Best Goalkeeper is a football award given annually since 1987 to the most outstanding goalkeeper as voted by the International Federation of Football History &amp; Statistics (IFFHS). The votes, in 1996, were cast by IFFHS's editorial staff as well as experts from 89 countries spanning six different continents.	
